BMI_chlstrl <- chlstrl %>% 
  mutate(height = (height * 0.0254)) %>% 
  mutate(weight = (weight * 0.454)) %>% 
  mutate(BMI = (weight/(height)^2))

Ejercicio 2 Funciones de R

Funcin cambioSigno

cambioSigno <- function(x) {
  lis <- (1:(length(x)-1))
  conteo <- 0
  
  for(i in lis) {
    if(x[i]>=0 & x[i+1] < 0) {conteo <- conteo + 1}
    
    else if (x[i] < 0 &x[i+1] > 0 ) {conteo <- conteo + 1}
  }
  return(conteo)
}

v <- c(-12, -19, 9, -13, -14, -17, 8, -19, -14)
cambioSigno(v)
## [1] 4

Modificar funcin para devolver la posicin del cambio de signo

cambioSignoPos <- function(x) {
  lis <- (1:(length(x)-1))
  conteo <- 0
  f = 1
  
  posicion <- c()
  
  for(i in lis) {
    if(x[i]>=0 & x[i+1] < 0) {conteo <- conteo + 1
    posicion[f] = (i+1)
    f = (f+1)}
    
    else if (x[i] < 0 &x[i+1] > 0 ) {conteo <- conteo + 1
    posicion[f] = (i+1)
    f= (f+1)}
  }
  return(posicion)
}
cambioSignoPos(v)
## [1] 3 4 7 8
